# Chitti optional LangSmith tracing — copy to `.env` (gitignored) to enable in dev.
#
# HOW IT WORKS (and why the key is split this way):
#   Chitti is a zero-backend static site. The LangSmith API key must never reach
#   the browser (the public bundle would leak it, and LangSmith's ingest isn't
#   browser-CORS-open). So the browser POSTs traces to a same-origin relay at
#   /langsmith/*, and the relay injects the key server-side. In `npm run dev`
#   that relay is the Vite dev proxy (astro.config.mjs), which reads the key
#   below from this file — server-side only, never inlined into client code.

# The secret. NO "PUBLIC_" prefix → server-only; used solely by the dev proxy.
LANGSMITH_API_KEY=lsv2_...

# Public (safe-to-inline) toggles read by the browser exporter (tracing.ts).
# Tracing is OFF unless this is exactly "1".
PUBLIC_LANGSMITH_TRACING=1
# The LangSmith project traces land in.
PUBLIC_LANGSMITH_PROJECT=chitti-dev
# Where the browser POSTs traces. Default is the same-origin dev-proxy path.
# To trace the DEPLOYED (GitHub Pages) site, stand up a serverless relay that
# holds the key and point this at it, e.g.
#   PUBLIC_LANGSMITH_INGEST_URL=https://<your-relay>.workers.dev/runs/batch
# PUBLIC_LANGSMITH_INGEST_URL=/langsmith/runs/batch
